  "text": "New knowledge on the genetic diversity and population structure of F. occidentalis in China as revealed in this study can help to improve management strategies. Strict trade quarantines and local eradication should be imposed to prevent further introduction and spread of the putative three source populations of F. occidentalis because of the high rates of gene flow from the three southwestern populations to the rest of the populations in China. Preventing contaminated plants from the putative source populations from being transported and population suppression or local eradication are crucial to eradicating this pest in other areas. To eradicate F. occidentalis from an area, it is necessary to reduce the population by various means, such as by using insecticides and chemical attractants, to a level below the Allee threshold or to apply biological controls to increase the Allee threshold [CITATION_1] . ",
